Driving on keyboard is easy, movement is smooth and the HD graphics are such that i couldnt even try to describe them here. Well deserving of its ratings on meta critic and accolades The online experience i wasn't happy with, trying to coordinate with friends to meet up after 1 was stuck in the tutorial was a nightmare, with no option to create a clan within the game itself. Overall GTA V is a big contender for game of the year for me, even with the 2 year wait and delays Rockstar did deliver. Heres looking forward to a great yeat in game titles!"]

And this game was definetly worth my wait. Everything looks amazing, runs smoothly, R*'s attention to details was really high and so on... But there are some things that are bugging me off: Single player: - The game sometimes starts in windowed mode. - First time loading is pretty darn long (1-2 minutes). - Map discoveries sometimes vanish for no reason (it becomes transparent as you have never been there). - If you enter a single player mode from online you are sometimes unable to switch characters and do missions so you have to restart your game. Online: - Huge loading time on start up and after leaving a lobby. - Very frequent server inaccessibility and crashing. Bad things aside, this is a very fun and addictive game which is optimised perfectly for almost every PC today. 10/10 Oh and a big thanks to my friend Definetly Not SkyDRO for testing this game on his Xbox 360. This version looks gorgeous, mate."]

Im glad Rockstar took their time in delaying the game and ironing out the kinks in the title. It was certainly well worth the wait. However, I do have one complaint, about the game and its about the online community. Now, Im no fan of hacking into games or cheating or anything like that, but the hackers that play this game are pretty bad when it comes to playing Grand Theft Auto Online. I dont get how some players can love the game so much that they simply have to cheat and get an advantage over other players or worse, causing mayhem by freezing players in the current servers system. I hope a proper system comes in place to prevent these players from causing such destruction to what feels like an almost perfect game. If youve played any game in the Grand Theft Auto franchise in the past, (which Im sure you have) I highly recommend you pick up this game immediately. You wont be disappointed, at least until you get into Grand Theft Auto Online. I have to admit, Rockstar bumping up the price to $79.99 on the day of the Steam Summer Sales and then knocking off 25% making it $59.99 again is a dirty move. Honestly, you've already made millions off of the fanbase that has already purchased the game for previous generation home consoles and the supposed next generation consoles, plus all of the hard working people like me who have purchased it for PC. Seriously, how much money do you need from us? Yes it's a great game, but Jesus, Christ.", '9.5/10 - I love this game too much']
